title: Hygge Girls™ Podcast
description:
Welcome to the Hygge Girls Podcast -- the podcast that's all about the cozy Danish practice of hygge and how it can bring warmth, connection, and well-being into your everyday life.

Childhood best friends, Madi Bares & Emma Roof, are your guide on a journey towards finding that elusive, yet attainable, sense of hygge.

Happiness isn't a destination, it's the beautiful result of a life well-lived. So, grab your comfiest blanket, pour yourself a glass of wine (or make yourself a mocktail), and join us every Monday for a giant run-on sentence as we dive deep into the world of a 20-something attempting to cultivate everyday happiness. Sure, our episodes may not be the most formal, but isn't that just a reflection of life's beautiful messiness? We're all on this journey together, and we're here to help you navigate the twists and turns with confidence.

From discussing health and wellness in a holistic manner to unraveling the impact of social media on our well-being, we're here to provide you with insights that resonate and advice that feels like you're chatting with your best friend.

Remember, the pursuit of happiness isn't about chasing an ideal; it's about savoring the present, connecting with others, and finding joy in the ordinary moments. With the Hygge Girls, you'll find yourself equipped with the tools and mindset to cultivate your very own hygge haven (& be sure to laugh along the way).

title: With One Tied Hand - The Buffalo Soldiers of World War II
description:
Though veterans of the United States of America liberated others worldwide at immense sacrifice, a little told American story is the unique liberation of the Tuscan people by the Buffalo Soldiers of WWII. After the War ended, these courageous men were sent home to a 'Jim Crow' America. 

Italian history is strikingly different. The impoverished, starving Tuscans feel as if they owe their lives to the Buffalo Soldiers, whom they lovingly dubbed 'Giganti Buoni' (Good Giants). An Italian eyewitness said, “They came down the mountain and freed us, and took care of us.” 

Ivan J. Houston, who was himself wounded in WWII, served in the Segregated 92nd Infantry Division, which bravely fought and pushed the German Nazis and Italian Fascists back behind  The Gothic Line. Tragically, these "Black Warriors" were also forced to fight the U.S. Army’s institutionalized racism, and even individual racist White officers who did not want them to succeed.

“That was just the way the Army was,” says Mr. Houston, retired CEO of America’s third largest African American-owned corporation. 

Between 1945 and 2011, Mr. Houston returned many times to Italy, meeting the Pope, revisiting his battlefields of old, and honoring his fallen comrades at the Florence-American Cemetery. Then, after writing the book, "Black Warriors: The Buffalo Soldiers of WWII, with Gordon Cohn, Mr. Houston was introduced by chance to many, many Italian Reenactors who treated him with warmth and respect. Through the hospitality of a gracious Italian woman, Mattea Piazzesi, a unique bond was formed between two families, the Houston's and the Piazzesi's. Ms Piazzesi had discovered Mr. Houston via his book.

Mr. Houston investigated missing casualty records with the help of local historians, who found the culprit was General Edward Almond, the racist commander (a fact acknowledged by the U.S. War College), who sent an African American Regiment into deadly battle without warning them to expect a heavy Nazi attack. This caused heavy casualties, which Almond then covered up. 

The documentary film, "With One Tied Hand" tells the stirring story of how Tuscan gratitude is finally shown to Mr. Houston, who on behalf of all Buffalo Soldiers is paraded and celebrated on a loving, yearly reenactment of the Liberation of Lucca, the 500-year-old walled city. The film also reveals moving personal stories from surviving eyewitnesses and their families. 

“I think this is the only instance in history where African-Americans have liberated another people,” Mr. Houston concludes.
author_name: Joe and Dayle Hartnett, Director & Producer of With One Tied Hand

title: From Here to Now: Immigrant Life in the States.
description:
From Here to Now aims to shed light on the many confusing, complex processes that are a part of the journey of immigrating to America, but we also hope to showcase the personal stories that emerge from such narratives. Where there are successful tales of obtaining H1B visas and receiving long-awaited green cards, there are also stories of hardship, struggle, and the resulting resilience and determination that arise. Where there is toil and strife, diligence and perseverance, there are also a multitude of other individuals who have experienced the same, and yet lived out their lives as immigrants in a completely different manner. Altogether, we hope to craft a well-rounded portrait of what it’s like to come to America and find yourself––slowly but surely––defining what it means to be American in your own right.

Let's talk about how some days you love who you are, but other days you low-key hate yourself. Let's talk about feeling sexy in your own skin. Let's talk about boobs, nipples, orgasms and buttholes. description: Wispit by Angela is a podcast designed by an African American female physician for the purpose of giving examples of personal life lessons, experiences, achievements, set backs, and wisps of wisdom.  The goal is to hopefully help someone, anyone, who desires more out of this life. Wispit is not a medical forum, but more of an encapsulation of  the experiences and words of wisdom of many people, some of whom are colleagues and friends, as a time capsule.   In this journey, I will interview people of various ages, gender, race, and socioeconomic status. Although this podcast is designed by a woman, it is not limited simply to women.  It is my hope that anyone, and everyone who tunes in, will be enriched, edified, spiritually touched, and moved to bypass the challenges of life,  and rise from the ashes of this limited existence to a higher elevation of thinking and creativity. Wispit abbreviated stands for Women and Wisdom in Socially Powerful and Interesting Times!  So, Let’s begin this journey together!  After all, we sometimes learn and listen more through the examples of others.

title: The Full of Beans Podcast
description:
The Full of Beans podcast, hosted by Han (your favourite crazy bean) is on a mission to reduce eating disorder stigma and increase ED awareness. Join Han weekly to hear the inspiring conversations she establishes with a range of individuals including those with personal experience and their loved ones as well as researchers, clinicians and charities who are all working to increase the understanding of eating disorders. 

Using Han's personal battle with atypical anorexia and body dysmorphia, as well as her MSc in Eating Disorders and Clinical Nutrition, Han uses her own knowledge to explore the experiences of like-minded individuals who are equally as passionate about sharing their own stories to increase the understanding of eating disorders. 

Eating disorders are crippling illnesses and this podcast aims to motivate individuals along their path of recovery. For more support please visit the BEAT or First Steps ED website, or visit your local GP. 

For more information, check out www.fullofbeansed.co.uk or follow the Full of Beans podcast at @thefobpodcast.

title: NON DOLET PODCAST
description:
NON DOLET nasce dalla volontà di un gruppo di Veterani delle Forze Speciali Italiane, supportati da membri della comunità militare e dalle Forze dell'Ordine, di creare un'Associazione che rappresenti la comunità di Patrioti che hanno fatto del DOVERE e dell'ONORE la propria ragione di vita. NON DOLET (cit. "non fa male") rappresenta il mindset che caratterizza ogni Veterano, basato sul senso di rinuncia alla propria persona in favore degli altri ignorando dolore e difficoltà. Lo scopo dell'Associazione è informare, condividere e valorizzare le battaglie passate, i caduti e tutti coloro che abbiano indossato una divisa. 
Questo Podcast è il primo del suo genere in Italia, i membri dell'Associazione intervistano Veterani che hanno vissuto esperienze traumatiche e hanno deciso di raccontarsi, facendo emergere storie di fratellanza, leadership, coraggio e crescita personale.

title: Humble Heroes
description:
Humble Heroes is really my tribute to the many awesome kids, parents, grandparents, celebrities and even pets in your life and mine that have shown us an extra dimension in living. So much news is bad news that tries to drag us down and elevate our fear response. Here’s the chance to turn the tables and celebrate good stuff. 

Maybe you have someone in your life like my Aunty Barb – just a wonderful role-model in handling hard times, never preachy, just had that extra dimension. No matter what went wrong, Aunty Barb would find a good side to it, never panicked, it was all God’s will. 

Here’s one example I remember well. In her later years when Barbara wasn’t as nimble or capable as she was in her earlier school librarian days, she decided to go back to England to see her brothers and sisters. As part of that exercise it meant catching a train from London to York with a couple of her brothers. During the trip Aunty Barb excused herself as she had to “go through”, her quaintly polite way of saying she needed to go to the toilet. After 55 minutes “going through” her brothers became concerned so they called on the guard to go and check on her. At first the guard couldn’t get the door open despite Aunty Barb’s faltering invitation to enter, but with mechanical help he managed to prise the door open. There was Aunty Barb sitting on the floor next to the toilet – she had fallen, passed out, woke up to find herself in this odd predicament but then relaxed knowing that God would send some nice person to help her out! No matter what the change, deterioration, frustration or loss of capacity in her life it was just taken in Aunty Barb’s stride on her way to Heaven! 

I haven’t found change that easy to handle and I don’t have Aunty Barb’s blind faith but I’ve loved life and loved the many cases and kids I’ve met - I’ve honestly drawn inspiration from them. If they can do it, so can I! These stories are my attempt to pay homage and respect to ordinary battlers achieving awesome outcomes with an extra dimension. 

The stories are not all serious – laughter is an important tool in mental health and many of my memories are about characters that just make me giggle when I think of them. Maybe you have a humble hero in your life who you’d like to acknowledge and celebrate. Well here’s your chance to submit stories. Look for the Submit your story tab above and share your story about your humble hero.

It’s my hope that together we can share heaps of humble heroes and that they can be an inspiration for each other. What a legacy that would be!

We do a weekly live stream on the Live To Roll YouTube channel which is now also available as a podcast! We discuss different topics pertaining to the disability/health care community and have new guests join us every week to share their stories and discuss the topics of the week.
Producer/host Shawn Fluke..
Co-host's Tom Conway and Bobby Rohan.
Tom, Bobby and I are all Quadriplegics from spinal cord injuries. Tom was injured at 4 years old and spent his whole life in a wheelchair and Bobby had his injury when he was 17. I was injured at 21 while snowboarding.. 
Women's Disability Show - Hosted by: Brianna Wheeler
Women's Show is on LIVE YouTube on the 1st & 3rd Thursday's of the month and discusses topics pertaining to women with disabilities.
You can hear more about our stories on the Live To Roll YouTube channel or on Instagram @livetoroll

title: Just Jay
description: Sometimes in life we go through things that we wouldn’t normally want to, but that’s apart of life. The good and the bad things that we go through are all a part of our journey. Each of us as individuals have our own specific journey. That is what makes our story and our lives different from anyone else. This podcast will be my platform to tell my story and take my audience on my journey through my life, all while healing and growing from my life’s events to make my future brighter. While I use this platform as a form of expression for myself, I will also be speaking on the topics that are often overlooked by today’s society, emphasizing the importance of shedding light on your past for a brighter future, and of course building a relationship with those who discover my podcast and my voice. My loved ones have always told me I have an amazing mind and voice of my own, and they’ve always encouraged me to use it. Now is my time. Welcome to Just Jay, the podcast.

De één wil beroemd worden en de ander ligt het liefst de hele dag in bed. Allebei hebben ze geen last van de zogenaamd onderdanige positie als vrouw, zijn ze altijd degene die ‘het mannetje’ dumpt of moet troosten als die het leven weer eens te moeilijk vinden. Allebei rechtse egoistische graaiers en kapitalisten voor wie de sky the limit is en allebei met linkse, zorgzame idealisten als vriendjes die naïef streven naar een eerlijker wereld en snel op hun teentjes getrapt zijn. Allebei een hekel aan mannen met een grote bek, maar nog meer aan vrouwen die niet voor zichzelf opkomen en zich onderdanig opstellen naar hun partner.

title: Jakarta D.C
description:
An English Podcast on the Daily Life in Indonesia. 

Brought to you by Television's Senior News Anchor Timothy Marbun.

This podcast takes you to talk about the latest going on in Jakarta and Indonesia from an Indonesian perspective, all performed in english. Dwell into a vast selection of topics, ranging from Pop-Culture, Digital Trends, up to Money and Business Opportunities by hearing it from the perspective of a seasoned journalist, and through talks with various interesting personalities found throughout Jakarta and beyond.

Tim has been a News Anchor and Broadcast Journalist for 15 years, and has reported major news events including National Elections, Social unrest in Thailand, Human Trafficking in Malaysia, and Massive Protests during the Arab Spring. Notable interviews include Palestinian PM, Twitter CEO, Instagram CEO, Coldplay, and Ed Sheeran.

Jakarta has been his home for the last 3 decades, after moving in from Norman Oklahoma where he spent part of his childhood. 

Tim also regularly moderates International events and seminars, including the IMF-World Bank Annual Meeting, Bali Democracy Forum, Indonesia-Africa Infrastructure Dialogue, and many more.

title: Trich Talks!
description: Let's talk about trich! And other BFRBs! Listen as Barbara Lally, author of The Trichster Diaries, interviews different guests about their experience with body-focused repetitive behaviors (BFRBs) like trichotillomania (the hair-pulling disorder), dermatillomania (the skin-picking disorder), and more. About 3% of total population experience BFRBs but they are rarely spoken about. Barbara is determined to bring more awareness to this class of disorders that have been with her since she was 10 years old. The stories of her guests are incredibly powerful and no matter if you have a BFRB or not, you will learn something about dealing with insecurity and self-acceptance.

title: Formula for Friends
description:
How real is stranger danger? And how do we make new friends if we're afraid of meeting strangers? Is there really a full-proof not-scary way to meet new people in the world? I honestly have no idea, but let's find out!
Formula for Friends is a conversational podcast where we interview old friends, new friends, best friends, frenemies, strangers, and literally everyone in between! 
Is there a formula to make deep and meaningful friendships? I don't know. Will we build some sturdy friendships? I certainly hope so.

title: Joost mag het weten
description:
Welkom bij de podcast 'Joost mag het weten'.  

De podcast waar je als luisteraar geen complete weergave krijgt, maar mag dwalen, om hier en daar een luikje open te maken; waarachter een versnipperd beeld wordt geschetst van het huidige afstudeer jaar te Sint Joost Breda, ART&RESEARCH 4 (2021). Het is juist die versnippering, die fragmentatie, die deze lichting typeert. 

Deze podcast legt de nadruk op de vertakkingen van het makerschap, haakt in elkaar waar nodig en deint mee op de golven van zij die al dobberend zoeken naar uitwisseling.

De structuur van de podcast is, net als de makers, aan verandering onderhevig. Er wordt gebruik gemaakt van bekende elementen maar is verder vrij in beweging, zo zijn er verschillende rubrieken, waarvan sommige terugkerend en andere eenmalig aanwezig.
author_name: Noëmi Francoise Hofstede; Anika Hochstenbach; Femke van Heijningen; Esther van Zoelen; Doris Kolpa; Hanne van Beek; Isa Janssen

Through in-depth interviews, this series will delve into the experiences, strategies, and mindset of thriving entrepreneurs, offering valuable lessons and inspiration for aspiring business leaders.

By uncovering the secrets behind their success, we aim to inspire and educate individuals interested in entrepreneurship, guiding them towards making informed decisions and pursuing their own business ventures.

title: Crazy Radio Stories
description: Radio didn't used to be all about corporate consolidation and out-of-market voicetrackers.  There was a time when we had full staffs! And with that many dysfunctional people in one building, some pretty wild stuff used to happen - both on and off the air. Chances are, if you worked in this business, you've got some crazy stories to tell. Crazy Radio Stories is the podcast that tells the world how radio USED to be.  Few rules, and in some cases, even fewer morals.  If you've got a crazy radio story to tell, email us - crazyradiostories@gmail.com.

title: #TodmanTalks
description: Welcome to #Todmantalks  Just sharing short thoughts, wisdom, and motivation from lessons and pain that grew me. Also providing a safe and inviting space to have deep and intimate conversations on difficult topics that are always overlooked and not discussed enough.

title: The Terez Leclerc podcast
description: My time in Burma started difficult, yet it became one of the most profound experiences I've had to date. I found myself alone in a closed country, with nothing familiar around me. Because of the extreme circumstances, Jesus became more real to me than ever before, and because there was no one else to rely on, I began to hear His voice loud and so clear. Thus we spent our time in conversation. This is a story that's never fully been told, its about how when everything was stripped away and I had nothing left but Jesus to hold on to, how He became more real to me than ever. It was my adventure with Holy Spirit. Raw, real yet true. I came back with new eyes, and a completely fresh perspective. All that mattered was Him. it was a time of growth and renewal. And the ministry there was something else. Everything that happened had a powerful effect on me, and one that would last a life time.

title: Actually Like
description: In an attempt to share more empathy in the world, I interview people of different stories. People who know what it is actually like doing or being something so that you can relate and empathize with something you might have never thought of before. title: Códigos de Liberdade
description:
Nesse podcast, Amanda fala de insights, mensagens, diálogos sobre bloqueios pessoais e traz convidados para falar sobre maneiras de reiniciar sua vida de maneira autêntica.

Amanda morou 10 anos nos Estados Unidos onde ela viveu a maioria de sua vida adulta, o que a condicionou de viver afastada da maneira mais alinhada para ela. Vindo de uma industria criativa, porém muito corporativa, ela identifica criatividade em tudo que vive. Criatividade significa autenticidade, e autenticidade vem da conexão com seu próprio ser. Amanda aprendeu que ao se libertar de condicionamentos, ela encontrou os códigos necessários para conexão com sua mais verdadeira forma de expressão.

Instagram: @codigosdeliberdade
Amanda Kunrath: @amandacocreates

title: Sonic Stories
description: Sonic Stories is a show where guests share their favorite songs and the stories behind them. Maybe it's motivated them to play their best game, helped them work through a tough life event, reminds them of a loved one, or just helps them get through the day. What's your jam?

title: Dialog Suwung
description:
Renungan puisi-puisi sakral untuk para perindu Tuhan.

Selamat datang para sahabat Suluk Suwung. Selamat datang di podcast Dialog Suwung ini bersama Pardamean Harahap dan Denny Turner.

Podcast ini lahir dari rekaman sesi-sesi mingguan instagram live di akun IG @suluksuwung. 

Kami berdua adalah sahabat spiritual yang bertemu awal tahun 2000an, dan bersahabat hingga sekarang. Berawal dari berguru kepada mursyid tariqah masing-masing, kami terus menjelajahi kedalaman kasih Ilahi dalam hidup keseharian.

Dalam konteks tasawuf, suwung mengandung makna kekosongan, makna kesadaran berketuhanan. Sering juga dimaknai dengan kata ma’rifat.
 
Kami melakukan dialog, renungan spontan di setiap sesinya. Tema pokok di setiap sesi adalah puisi sakral, ataupun sistematika inspiratif, yang kami gali dari berbagai tradisi.

Melalui dialog spontan ini, kami berkomunikasi dari hati ke hati dengan anda semua. Energi kita semua, adalah doa agar kita dihantarkan oleh Tuhan, menuju Tuhan.

Dialog ini dihadiahkan kepada sesama pejalan yang senantiasa rindu akan Tuhan.

title: El Podcast de JP Martinez
description: Un día estaba en mi cuarto, ya era de noche, y na más no me podía dormir. Estaba bien emocionado, ilusionado, y pensando en todas las posibilidades fregonas que podría traerme un podcast. - - Estaba emocionado y todavía no había dado ni un paso, sólo pensar en la posibilidad. Agarré mis 4 meses de ahorros y compré los micrófonos, un tripié nuevo para que ya no se me cayera la luz, y hoy estoy aquí, cumpliendo uno de mis sueños. - - Desde chiquito me acuerdo que me quedaba platicando con las chicas que nos ayudaban con la limpieza de la casa. Chiquito chiquito, unos 6 años. Una vez una chica me platicó toda la aventura de su papá en su intento de pasarse a Estados Unidos sin documentos - - Me fascinaba oírla, preguntar, y entender cosas nuevas!! Ya luego llegaba mi mamá a decirme que me fuera a dormir. - - Creo que el espíritu de ser preguntón lo sigo tendiendo, y eso me emociona un buen!! - - Si te gustaría ayudarme a cumplir este sueño que me trae bien emocionado date algún capítulo, estoy seguro te va a fascinar!

title: It's Juxtaword
description:
Division seems to be all around us right now. Opposing sides. Contrasting view points. However, we know through art and literature, that contrast can bring beauty and wholeness.  Life's juxtapositions.

Through this podcast, Rachel and Megan use their love of words and analogies to get a bird's-eye view of the masterpiece in which we all play a part.

Join us for each episode as we discuss a word, what it means to us, and the power we can gain from it.

Personligt føler jeg selv, at jeg har en del tanker som teenager, og ved at dele dem højt, håber jeg at kunne skabe en følelse om, at man faktisk ikke er alene om ens tanker, og på den måde skabe et slags frirum. Jeg håber at du vil lytte med, og hvis du har nogen kommentar til episoderne, så endelig skriv til mig på instagram: Seraphine.selawry - Knus herfra <3

description: The impact of truth, healing, and life experiences is shared with an open heart. Exploring the heart space and journey to self. Opening up the throat chakra by speaking on all curiosities and synchronicities. What does it mean to live a "spiritual life" ? What is a spiritual awakening? What does the term mystic mean to you? Do you share your spiritual beliefs & experiences? Why is it scary to speak your truth? How do you go inward? What does it mean to protect your energy?

title: Naturalies
description:
Naturalies.
 
My name is Samantha-Jo, I am the host for this amazing podcast that I am hoping save souls. My reasoning for starting this podcast came about after I gave my life to Christ on July 11, 2021. I started finding myself constantly want to talk about my struggles (HOT: humble, open & transparent), the things that have given me strength, the things God has done for me & most importantly the things I know that God has for me. I know you're thinking "oh here we go with some religious podcast" but I'm asking that you look deeper than that. I am a Christian & yes I pray this podcast changes lives in ways beyond my belief but if its not enough to convince you to stay I will also mention the other things I am that God has allowed me to be. I am a single Mother of 4, YES FOUR amazing boys who at the end of this year will be 12, 6, 4 & 2. I am a business owner (if you have instagram JosCraftShack & Sheis.waisted).  I am also a nurse, I have been for almost 4 years now. So again if religion isnt enough to convince you to stay then stick around for the other things I have to offer.

Why Naturalies?
I recently (1 year ago) left a very toxic relationship after 8 years & literally started completely over in the middle of the pandemic with all 4 children. I literally built my own kitchen table, tv stand, coffee table, my bed & childrens bed & started over knowing only what I thought I knew. Black women have been placed in boxes all of our lives. "Starting over is harder than you think so you should probably stay" "You cant do it without this person or that person", "You have to act this way, its not lady like to do it that way", "You cant jump out on faith because nobody in our family has done that", "You cant be better than what you come from", "your idea isnt good enough to take you there" ALL LIES, LIES, AND MORE LIES THAT PEOPLE HAVE PLACED ON BLACK WOMEN & LADIES YOU DO NOT HAVE TO AGREE TO MEET ANY STANDARD YOU, YOURSELF, DID NOT SET! This is my safe haven for black women, no matter what you look like, your body size, your bank account or profession, single mom, married mom, in a bad situation, left a bad situation LISTEN I do not care. Come, let your hair down, act the way you want to act even if it doesn't make sense to anyone else, cry a little, heal a lot & know that this is a sisterhood.

Im so ready for this journey. I love you ladies.

title: My Manifesting Mindset
description:
Hello Everyone and Welcome!

I am so excited to be on this new journey with you. I have dealt with anxiety and depression for so long. I have felt so alone for a huge part of it. I have worked so hard to find things that would help, but have had such a hard time sticking to them. 

My goal is to make this podcast as relatable as possible. If there is anything in specific you would like me to talk about, please feel free to email me or DM me, I am always here.

Email: mymanifestingmindset@gmail.com
Instagram: @mymanifestingmindset

Always remember you are never alone. I hope everyone has a beautiful and amazing day. Go out there and shine.

title: Front Porch Diaries
description:
Hey y’all!

I’m a God fearing, lover of Jesus mother of 2 {{birth}} 1 {{stepson}}
blessed wife of a handsome, hardworking husband.

Front Porch Diaries was created on August 26, 2020 on our front porch here on the creek of the Pamlico River.  Here on the porch, I have experienced despair, wisdom, faith, love, compassion, forgiveness, inspiration, hope and freedom.  But most of all God.  

Music is also my medicine.  It helps sort out all kinds of emotions that I may be going through.

I’ll be sharing devotions from inspirational women like Joyce Meyers, and reading straight from the Bible.  Share my testimonies, and stories, my life with my family- which is pretty amazing.  But far from perfect.  

My dream is to bring more people together through compassion and honesty and finding out who God truly created me to be. 

For more Front Porch Diaries
Join Front Porch Diaries on Facebook
Subscribe on YouTube

Much love to you all!  May blessings flow your way!

description: Welcome to Steps, a podcast celebrating people and their stories. Far too often we don't give people the opportunity to share their journey. Where they've come from, what they've overcame and the amazing things that have happened to them in their lives. That's what we are going to do on Steps. We will have real conversations with real people to understand how they have gotten to this place in time. Confucius said, "The journey of 1000 miles starts with a single step." So, Let's start this journey.

The journey really started when at the ripe old age of 47 I joined the motherhood fraternity, which I tell you is a different ball game entirely, parenting truly brings unexpected surprises.

I want to speak up about the issues that concern me because they may affect my child when she grows up, hoping my voice will multiply and move us into positive action.

Join me as I chat over coffee on life, parenting, books I'm reading, and all that takes my fancy.

What does wellness look like with no health insurance and $0.05 to your name? 

That's a question that popped into my head in 2020. With the surge of COVID-19 and social distancing, I was a broke college student, and I was "po" when it came to balancing the areas of my life. By "po" I mean, I had all the information in the world, but applying it was a different thing. My mindset needed a lot of work. Over the last 2 years, I've strived to live out a more balanced life, and I want to share my journey with people that know what it's like to stretch a penny as my Mom calls it. This podcast explores the areas of wellness in relation to social issues and personal growth.

title: The Memorial of a Shy Black Girl
description: Hey y'all! My name is DaAujana and welcome to my spoken word diary. Inspiration for this diary was drawn from a multitude of sources, but the main one being high school and my first semester of college. I've always been shy and introverted and isn't a bad thing by any means, but it has caused me to feel an overwhelming amount emotions that have been not so good along the way. The biggest thing I've had to cope with is being alone and not feeling so confident sometimes - and because of that, it has caused me in the past and in the present to withstand what feels to be an uphill battle. Thus, I want to share my stories with all of you because we are going through our own ups and downs. We are all impacted by the actions of our world and instead of remaining shy and silent, I want to use my voice to empower others through sharing my own stories(both serious and ridiculous ones) and truly journey through the process of stepping out of ones embarrassment, shyness, shame, etc and truly being who you are. This journey is also like a mini journal for me to spill out and say all of the things that I have wanted to express for so long, but hadn't because I was too afraid to- I can only hope that through my courage and my words that it will encourage you all to feel empowered to truly be unapologetically yourself and slowly show people the real you and step into your true prime.⚡️

title: Muslim Birthwork with Doula Alqabalia
description:
A series of unique interviews and recounts providing inspirational insight into pregnancy, birth and beyond within the Muslim community. 

Hosted by Amy, the face behind Doula Alqabalia; a Muslimah Birthworker currently based in the East Midlands, UK. 

The series sets out to shed light upon the misconstrued conceptions, assumptions and discrimination that Muslim women and their families face in everyday life. 

The trials and struggles that Muslim people face during the antenatal, birth and postnatal period are highlighted, whether they opt in for access to the maternity services, or not, as the case may be! 

In a time when physiological birth and traditional practices and values around birth are being dissolved, we have a duty to stand up and reclaim our birth rights for both our women and children. 

Providing first-hand information and experiences as an actively involved Birth and Postpartum Doula and Holistic Birthkeeper, Amy brings a raw, real and radical Muslim perspective to the scene.

title: Voz
description:
Voz es más que un poema, es un grito a la libertad y el amor por toda la humanidad.

Poetas del Pueblo

Las motivaciones que predominan en mi, para escribir, son unos fuertes sentimientos de libertad, solidaridad, respeto y amor por todo lo que tenga vida. Toma mi poesía, si no te gusta deja la ir. Si te agrada, llámame, te regalare mi voz. Nací en un pueblo costero al sur de Andalucía, mis inquietudes y mi forma de ver la vida me pusieron siempre al lado de la lucha por las libertades. 
El grueso de los poemas que en esta página se recitan, son de mi autoría, hago también podcast de poesía, recitando poemas de autores de habla castellana, o no, con la particularidad de que recitaré, principalmente  a los poetas Andaluces, excepción de varios de los mismos, al tener que recitar a poetas andaluces, el formato será distinto. El léxico cambia considerablemente, espero lo disfruten al igual que yo, haciendo este trabajo.

title: Confessions of a Rock'n'Roll Cameraman
description:
New episodes every Thursday! 

cornrc.com

In the 1980s, Culture was being shaped by immerging digital video technology.  Tony Wannamaker was one of the founders of Much Music “The Nation's Music Station”. The  messages playing out in music videos. Being a blue-collar cameraman gave Tony the ability to access and document this cultural revolution through the camera lens while adding to the cultural shift itself through his visual reporting.  
As Pat Canavan interviews Tony about his 40-year career, the podcast delves into the Canadian identity in pop culture outside of the US narrative. We get an inside look at Tony's adventures around the world, including encounters with celebrities like Sidney Poitier, musicians David Bowie, The Rolling Stones, Madonna, Lenny Kravitz and more. Then we will dive deep with sharks of unknown names or celebrity status, travel to Africa to shoot the BIG 5 and meet the Masai Prince and even explore a near-death experience.

title: FANG
description:
FANG is a platform to share our lives as African Americans who grew up on traditional Nigerian values in Brooklyn, NY. After accomplishing the life long goal of our immigrant-parents to have a Bachelors degree we are now ready to live the great life that having a degree is suppose to reward us with.  Yet months and years have gone by and we are still wondering  what’s next; marriage, careers, businesses, toilet paper shortage, spiked gas prices? With COVID-19 making its debut not to long after walking the virtual graduation stage, we are taking the opportunity to really sit, be still and think;  what the heck are we supposed to be doing right now? What do  we want to come from our lives because what we were expecting has not revealed itself as promised? We were told by our elders to do what you love and you’ll never work a day in your life. And chile, we do not want to work!

FANG stands for “First American-Nigerian Generation” and the creators are Mukrimat & Rebecca.

#polskipodcast #realizmmagiczny #światłocienie #pisarka #kultura #literaturapiękna #magiawrzeczywistości

Rzeczywiście, magicznie, oczywiście nieoczywiście➰
Ze strefy światła i cienia🤍🖤
Życiowo, baśniowo, romantycznie, nostalgicznie, logicznie, dosłownie i w przenośni💫

„Światłocienie” to przestrzeń wyjątkowa.
Dla każdego i o każdym. Głębia istoty ukryta w prostocie. Najprawdziwsze emocje i przeżycia. Dualizm życia, wydobywanie blasku z ciemności.
Słowa, myśli i refleksje ubrane w metafory. Rzeczywistość i ukryta w niej magia. Miłość do świata, do ludzi, do siebie.
O doświadczaniu chwili, o ulotności. Tak jak w świecie, wszystko się w tej przestrzeni miesza. Sięga do głębi, wykroczy poza horyzont. Choć osadzone w rzeczywistości, to jednak z innego wymiaru.
Światłocienie.

Updated on May 25, 2022: used “season numbers” to differentiate English & Chinese contents. See below:
S22 中文 - 雪士達山與我
S11 The mountain is calling, i must go.


Updated on April 30, 2022: i was guided to rename the show as "Journeys to Mt Shasta".


Mt Shasta is a magical place that i call “HOME” especially in the spiritual way. Ever since my first visit Mt Shasta back in October 2011, my entire life has been shifting and transforming to the levels that i could never ever imagine how my life has becoming now and continuing to evolve to be better and greater.

Starting podcasting “Mt Shasta and i” is one of my latest assignments from Mt Shasta, so the Mother Earth Heart energy could reach out to the world further and influence more people’s lives to shifting our consciousness as a whole.

If you know about Mt Shasta, you probably heard of Lemuria, Telos, High Priest Adama, Master Saint Germain and so many more… And yet, “Mt Shasta and i” is going to be based on my personal experience with Mt Shasta. To share my real life transformation examples will be the main attribute of this show. In addition to just my own storytelling, there will be soul families and friends to share their profound enlightenment experience with Mt Shasta. 

i am so excited about this new way of storytelling, instead of trying to publish “Mt Shasta and i” book 1, 2,3, which i started a few years back and somehow i did not go too far and just suddenly stopped.  Now i believe it’s time. Thank you, Mt Shasta and the Spirits. i am in gratitude!

i am also starting a Chinese / Mandarin version of "Mt Shasta and i" show. They will not be the exact same duplicates with only language difference. They will have their own uniqueness individually. 

i understand having two shows at the same time is a huge task, but i have always feel that i want to do both since the beginning. Now, i just need to start the first step and slowly build up the momentum. Constantly reminding myself not to push myself too hard. Learn to pace myself and remember to breathe.

i am a going-with-the-flow kind of guy, so it is not going to be in chronological order about my story. i will just follow the guidance from Mt Shasta and the Spirit!

description:
The Sperber Prize Podcast is a show highlighting some of the most influential reporters and journalists around the world through their biographies and autobiographies. Join us as we speak with Sperber Prize nominees to talk about their lives as reporters, their book-writing process, and the state of journalism.


The Sperber Prize is given in honor of Ann M. Sperber, the author of the excellent biography of Edward R. Murrow, Murrow: His Life and Times (Fordham University Press). The book received numerous awards for its meticulous research and finely crafted writing and was a finalist in 1987 for the Pulitzer Prize. Through the generous support of Ann’s mother, Lisa, the prize was established to promote and encourage other outstanding biographies and memoirs related to the field of print and electronic journalism.

title: Lets chat about Death
description:
Welcome to "Let's Chat About Death," the podcast that fearlessly explores the weird and wonderful things we do when it comes to the end of life. Join us on this intriguing and sometimes surprising journey as we delve into the diverse customs, rituals, and beliefs surrounding death and dying from around the globe.

In each episode, we'll unravel the fascinating traditions that have evolved over centuries, shedding light on how different cultures and societies approach the inevitable. From ancient burial practices to modern-day funeral innovations, we'll uncover the unique and unexpected ways people celebrate, mourn, and commemorate the departed.

But it's not all about solemnity; we'll also embrace the lighter side of the topic. We'll discuss the quirky and unconventional ways people choose to leave their mark on the world, from unusual last wishes to creative and eccentric memorial services that celebrate life in the most extraordinary ways.

Beyond the cultural and individual aspects, we'll delve into the broader impact of death on society, examining how it has influenced art, literature, music, and even shaped our cities' landscapes. Through insightful interviews with experts, historians, and individuals with personal experiences, we'll explore the profound philosophical and existential questions that arise when confronting mortality.

While "Let's Chat About Death" tackles profound themes, we aim to create an open and welcoming space for our listeners to engage with the topic thoughtfully and with empathy. Our goal is to foster a greater understanding of death's role in the human experience and to celebrate the diversity of approaches to this universal truth.

So grab a cup of tea, settle in, and join us for thought-provoking conversations, heartwarming stories, and moments of laughter as we navigate the strange and beautiful tapestry of life's final chapter together. "Let's Chat About Death" promises to be a unique and unforgettable exploration of the human experience like no other.

description:
Der Podcast "Vom Gangster zum Bürger" ist ein medienpädagogisches Projekt vom Heinrich-Wetzlar-Haus der Jugendeinrichtung Schloss Stutensee gGmbH.

Das Heinrich-Wetzlar-Haus, kurz HWH, ist ein Angebot der U-Haft-Vermeidung gemäß § 71,2 und § 72,4 JGG. Hier werden seit Juni 1984 männliche delinquente Jugendliche im Alter von 14 bis 18 Jahren mit dem Leitgedanken „Erziehungshilfe statt Untersuchungshaft“ betreut.

Ziel des Podcast ist es nicht, True Crime Geschichten zu erzählen, sondern den Blick über den Tellerrand zu wagen. Den Jugendlichen soll die Möglichkeit gegeben werden, sich von dem Bild des „Gangsters“ frei zu machen, indem sie von ihren Geschichten, Emotionen und Biografien erzählen. Die Jugendlichen sollen damit die Chance erhalten, als junge Menschen gesehen zu werden, die nicht nur delinquentes Verhalten zeigen, sondern auch ganz einfache Jugendliche mit all ihren Facetten und u. a. auch mit ihren individuellen Schicksalen sind. Dies soll der häufigen Stigmatisierung der Jugendlichen im Heinrich-Wetzlar-Haus entgegenwirken und die Jugendlichen für alle Zuhörer greifbarer und nahbarer machen. 

Neben den persönlichen Geschichten der Jugendlichen gibt der Podcast „Vom Gangster zum Bürger“ auch Einblicke in den HWH-Alltag und in das pädagogische Konzept der Vermeidung von Untersuchungshaft. Die Themen „Straffällige Jugendliche, Straftaten, Haft, neue Wege gehen, neue Perspektiven schaffen“ werden aus verschiedenen Blickwinkeln (straffällige Jugendliche, pädagogische Mitarbeitende, Anwälte, Richter o. ä.) betrachtet. Damit möchte der Podcast zudem Transparenz schaffen sowie Aufklärung und Prävention leisten. Die Podcast-Folgen, die verstärkt in Interview-Form gehalten sind, wobei die Jugendlichen in die Rollen des Interviewenden als auch des Interviewten schlüpfen, sollen junge Menschen darin bestärken, ihre Ziele zu verfolgen sowie die Chance auf ein gutes Leben zu ergreifen. Humorvolle Berichterstattung aus dem HWH als auch reine Erzählungen sorgen darüber hinaus für Abwechslung. 

Intro + Outro: Lovely Em 150 Beat von "Goose Park Productions", zur Verfügung gestellt von BUFARAH e. V. (BUFARAH BEATZ)

With a growing listener base on Instagram and radio (Big FM Shillong & Aizawl), Aditya is emerging as one of India's pioneering music podcasters, focusing exclusively on interacting with internationally acclaimed musicians. In just a year, he has interviewed renowned legends like Joe Satriani, Cindy Blackman Santana, Phil Perry, Bob James, Lee Ritenour, Doyle Bramhall II, Eric Martin, Nathan East, Richard Bona, Paul Carrack, Victoria Canal, and many others.

Season 1 comprised over 50 remarkable episodes, and Season 2 promises even more by featuring international legends and music industry experts from India. This season also introduces a new dimension with festival edition podcasts in the country. Get ready for an extraordinary journey into the world of music!

title: Real life everyday issues from a 'regular person's' POV
description:
My podcasts are about the everyday life struggles some of us encounter and are forced to deal with on our own. My podcasts are for people like myself, the 'underdogs', people who go through things in life who have to fight their battles alone, who don't have anyone else except themselves for (emotional) support of any kind. If you are a person who's faced with more trials and tribulations in your everyday life than the average person does, then these podcasts are for you. If you suffer from mental health issues that stem from wrong that's been done to you and have no one to talk to or you think or feel that no one understands what you're going through, if you feel your life consists of nothing but unfair and negative challenges that you always seem to end up on the loosing end of & your constantly misjudged by those around you - especially people you thought would understand, these podcasts are for you. 
Life isn't always fair, that's just the way it goes, but for some people life seems to be truly and constantly unfair all the way around. After a while it takes a serious toll on you & it affects us in unimaginable ways, mentally, physically, emotionally & sometimes even sociably & when you don't have anyone except yourself to rely on, times that are already difficult to deal with or get through become 10 times harder. We don't always have the right answers to the issues that life can bring, we just do the best we can with what we have - & sometimes all we have is ourselves to get us by & if you know like I know, even though all we have in the end are ourselves, the flip side (truth) is, no one is meant to get through this thing called life alone, but for some of us, people like myself, we're forced to. My podcasts aren't for the 'elite', meaning, it's not for people who don't have these kind of problems or people who have been through something at some point in their life & have come out on 'top' & it all worked out to their benefit in the end, no. These podcasts are for 'us', the 'underdogs' - people who fight just to get by but just can't seem to 'get ahead' because everything that life continues to serve up to them is just one fucked up issue after another that continues to knock you down. Of course when you get knocked down you get back up, you have to, but people need to realize that even though you get back up after being knocked down, every knock down leaves you wounded & when getting knocked down is one right behind the other, as you continue to 'get back up', you're not getting up with as much strength as you had before & when it continues to happen (& often), yes you get back up, but the fight in you continues to weaken which means, the next 'knock down' is going to take more of a toll on your inner strength than you may have to give. 
People who don't have these types of issues, or have been through things in their life where getting up wasn't as difficult after a few 'knock downs' will not be able to relate to my podcasts, & that's ok because these podcast are not for you so the judgements, feel free to keep to yourself or go enjoy another channel that applies to you. People LOVE judging others, especially when your problems aren't theirs but that's not right. My podcasts offer compassion & understanding to the 'underdogs' - people who's life's are unfairly judged by others - other's usually sitting in a very comfortable position who have the audacity to look or talk down on or about others who are not as 'fortunate' as they are. Believe me when I tell you that I understand how it feels to be an 'underdog' & my podcasts are for us.

Disclaimer: I am no scholar, I am no Dr. Phil, I am just a regular everyday person who's dealing with life and the issues I'm dealt the best way I can, alone. Although alone is not the way I choose to deal with my life issues, it's the way I'm forced to deal with them.

title: Real Talk for Real Women: Let the Healing Begin
description:
Stories of Honor, Hope & Healing

The beautiful women that you will hear about in these heartfelt stories are deserving of honor. We call them Phoebes. In Romans Chapter 16, Apostle Paul describes Phoebe as a servant, friend, confidant, and helper of many. Phoebes are women who are placed in others' lives to fill those gaps that life may have caused and are motivated by love and a servant's attitude. They showed up in the lives of ordinary people at the right place and time to help them navigate the muddy waters of life. In the podcasts, you will hear stories about victory over addiction, abuse, teenage pregnancy, loss and so much more that life throws our way. The beautiful souls you will hear from are sharing from the heart -- unscripted -- about their Phoebe(s) and how they made it to the other side of their struggles. The presence and value of Phoebe may not be realized for some time, but when the pieces of their life's story are revisited, their impact is acknowledged. Honor, hope, and healing...that is what you will get. Sit back, relax, and enjoy Real Talk for Real Women: Let the Healing Begin!

title: Stories of Hope | Junction 42
description:
Our aim is simple: to see the lives of offenders and their communities visibly transformed through support, empowerment, and opportunity. Here, you'll hear real inspirational, yet raw conversations which include shame, brokenness, failure, forgiveness, redemption and hope. This is Stories of Hope.

We at Junction 42 are passionate about making a real difference in the lives of those who are most vulnerable and marginalized in our society. We know that we cannot achieve our mission alone, and we are incredibly grateful for any support that we receive from individuals like you.

Whether you choose to volunteer your time, make a donation, or simply spread the word about our work, you are making a real and tangible impact in the lives of those we serve. Please visit our website at www.junction42.org or give us a call at 0191 2612684 to learn more about how you can get involved with our work. And if you would like to support our mission through a donation, you can do so by visiting www.junction42.org/donate. Together, we can make a difference and create a brighter future for all.

Thru the normalizing of truthtelling, these stories are shared for the sake of our collective healing and legacy that we choose to live and leave.

title: The Between the Pages Podcast
description:
We live in a world where we tend to focus on the mountain top and valley moments that life brings us. The beginning, biggest victories, character climax, and loss that each chapter of life can bring. When we are on the mountain top we worship God, and when we are in the valley, we cry out to God. 

But, we live most of our life in the day to day, where we just go through the motions. So how do we keep up a bold faith "between the pages" of life? 

That is what "Between The Pages" is all about! We are challenging the conversations to dive deeper in how we can live out our faith. 

Join us every other Wednesday as we talk to different guests, team members, community leaders about topics that will leave you feeling challenged and encouraged! 

Continue the conversation each week on our Instagram @boldlyseeking

description: In this Podcast series, Lizzie Bee reads from her personal diary, starting from the beginning of her healing journey. Be sure to tune in every Friday (or every other) to catch a new episode of Open Book starring Lizzie Bee and her Diary, and taking listeners with her on this wild journey.

title: Drinking While Sober

She understands that we are all human and it’s okay to make a mistake or be late or listen to this while you sit on the toilet. The world isn’t going to end. Be in control! Be you and great!

title: Forced Nostalgia
description: Content Creation boomed in the 2010s and continues to flourish on the internet. Podcasts, YouTube, Twitch, personalized video websites, and so much more circulate in a massive over-inflation of content for the consumer. We have all tried to create something for the potential market, yet we only hear from the success stories: those who surpassed tens of thousands of loyal community members. What about the failures? The failed year-long attempt that only brought dozens of subs? What can the learnings of failed content creators do to benefit you? They say you learn more in defeat than victory, and Jordan and Hunter look to do just that.

description: 简介：我们是三位在读生物医学女博士，坐标北欧，本着科学态度探讨科研玄学，采用摆烂策略探索知识边界，偶尔沉迷八卦，时常认真搞笑，始终专注个人演技提升。此节目尺度较宽，信息量较大，笑声过于频繁，请择情收听。如果大龄未婚女性有意见，也请出门左转，不送。

title: Life Agency WTF
description:
Life Agency WTF is a podcast. Real life, real friends, real life experiences, real talk. 

Lisa and Danielle are in Phoenix Arizona and are just like YOU... real women with the same day to day experiences on everything from family, friendships, business, entrepreneurship, and plenty of WTF moments we all encounter.

We share personal and relatable stories on all the things, and invite you to listen in, reach out, give suggestions on topics, and basically just FRIEND with us. You will hear us go deep, light, and all the in between, all while adding comedic value at no extra cost. 
We hope you have as much fun listening as we do creating this!

title: The Road to Rediscovery
description: Life is a journey. Along the way, we hit tight turns, inclines, and rough terrains where lessons are presented to us. Some of these we discover and learn, and others are presented to us AGAIN later in life. Will we just ignore them and move on, or REDISCOVER the lesson, and grow? Aubrey shares lessons he's learned on his journey, and chats with extraordinary people who share their amazing stories as well. If you like what you hear, please subscribe to my channel and/or feel free to leave feedback.

title: linkse ratten de podcast
description:

Ze zijn beide werkzaam in de (radicaal) linkse politiek en beginnen elke aflevering met een ethisch dilemma. Tot slot wordt elke aflevering beëindigt met wie al dan niet de 'Raadshunk' van de week is. Luister mee naar de gedachtenspinsels van twee twintigers die de term 'linkse ratten' hebben toegeëigend van de rechtse rakkers. Bedankt, hé! Het bekt best lekker.

'linkse ratten de podcast' is een DIY-podcastproductie. Het wordt steeds beter. Beloofd.

title: The Highlife Uncut
description:
What is the High Life Uncut? 

The high Life Uncut is a podcast that discusses the lives of those that work in what is dubbed as Syd,Aus and/or Australia’s ‘Top Tier’ corporates. 


Who are the Podcast hosts Jen & Alex? 

Jen & Alex are Gen Z 9-5 corporates in a ‘Top Tier’ Australian bank. They are ambitious corporates who have combined 10-12 years experience across professional services, tourism, start-up, tech, fast moving consumer goods (fmcg) and financial services. 


Why The High Life Uncut? 

Jen & Alex realised there are conversations that we are afraid to strike up at times outside of the workplace or even with close friends. 

They talk through topics that can be uncomfortable to discuss from a male and female perspective. 

It’s about the fine art of balance between your personal life blurring into your career. 

Grab yourself a beveragino and find a spot to kick back so you can listen to The High Life Uncut.

title: Radically, Rachael
description:
Radically, Rachael "The Modern Mystic" is an Intuitive Life Coach and Spiritual practitioner in the Chicagoland Suburbs.

Once upon a time, Rachael was a bullied child from a dysfunctional home. A former Christian who spent the first decade of her adult career as an elementary school educator. After coming out in her early 20’s, marriage, and a divorce - her life today looks Radically different.

In a modern Cinderella story, Rachael “Fairy Godmother-ed” herself and took charge of the storyline. Laugh, cry and cringe along with Rachael and her friends to stories that are sure to make your jaw drop. As she awakens to some major themes throughout her life, you will hear and see the way that SPIRIT has been present all along.

Radically, Rachael the Podcast begins as the story of a woman's journey unraveling church camp "purity culture" and embraces "Sex and the Suburbs" as a Divorcee. Rachael explores it all! From Sex to Spirituality....her LGBTQ coming out experience, purity culture, deconstruction, relationships, and co-parenting as a bonus "mom" character.

The Radically, Rachael podcast features narrative stories, raw conversations with special guests, guided meditations & affirmations, and even excerpts from Rachael's diary.

Follow Rachael on Instagram and TikTok @RadicallyRachael or visit her website www.radicallyrachael.com to connect!

If you are a #justagirlfriend or Bonus "Mom" Character yourself, check out the Just a Girlfriend Club - Bonus Character Welcome Facebook Group.

https://www.facebook.com/groups/2452256038262018/

rad·i·cal - adj: especially of change or action, relating to or affecting the fundamental nature of something; far-reaching or thorough.

title: Life After. . .THAT!
description: What was THAT? This podcast will focus on survival and pushing forward after life events, tragic or not. Life after illness, Life after abuse, Life after a career, Life after whatever else happens! Season 1 focuses on the survivors of Amyotrophic Lateral Sclerosis (ALS)--widows, widowers, partners, friends, siblings, children, etc. Each of our participants will have 2 episodes, the first being their story--Life AFTER the diagnosis, the onslaught of the changing dynamics of the disease, and how it changed relationships, and life. The second episode for each story will focus on Life After THAT monster and how they are moving on or not and what might help themselves and others. In other words, how are they now carrying on? ALS is considered rare, yet it kills tens of thousands in the United States annually and many more worldwide. Most ALS patients live 2-5 years from diagnosis, but not all. Regardless, the body movements die off while the mind usually stays vibrant. Most of those affected wouldn’t wish the disease on their worst enemy and would actually prefer cancer over ALS...because except in rare cases, there’s at least a chance to survive with the other. In either case, loved ones are changed forever, and suffer from PTSD, depression, etc. The importance of spreading awareness of the disease is important, but so is acknowledging what the caretakers and loved ones have been through. This season provides that opportunity, a sounding board if you will, and hopefully what my late husband, also a victim of ALS, encouraged...”Keep on keepin’ on because being sad or mad will not do you any good. Be happy.”

En cada episodio se podrá escuchar un fragmento de su poesía considerada en el siglo XIX como locura. Nuestro autor casi la mitad de su vida estuvo "encerrado" en una torre, donde podía contemplar la naturaleza con una magnífica panorámica y un espíritu sensible y romántico. 

Johann Christian Friedrich Hölderlin nace el 20 de marzo de 1770 en Lauffen am Neckar Wurtemberg, y muere el 7 de junio de 1843 en Tubinga, Reino de Wurtemberg.

Te invito a ponerte cómodo y escuchar esta delicia poética.

title: salat alles - bissien scharf
description: Ein Podcast über die Erfahrungen des Lebens. Jedes Gefühl darf gefühlt werden - nichts ist zu peinlich, zu groß oder zu klein. Alles ist gut, genauso wie es ist. Die Generationen vor uns mussten in erster Linie überleben, arbeiten und existieren - in ihrem Kosmos waren Begriffe wie Therapie, Sexismus, Spiritualität und Co. so weit entfernt, dass wir nun das Trauma der letzten drölf Generationen aufarbeiten dürfen. Wir haben gleichzeitig aber auch das große Privileg unseren Alltag und das Leben täglich zu hinterfragen und über Uns hinauszuwachsen. Eine Revolution in Bewegung zu setzen und mit unserer Kraft und dem neuen Bewusstsein Großes zu bewirken. Von wegen „früher war alles besser“, wir bauen uns eine fantastische neue Zukunft, in der wir ausprobieren, gewinnen, scheitern und dazulernen dürfen. Aus tiefstem Herzen lieben und es dann wieder kläglich brechen lassen, um irgendwie immer mehr zu verstehen, was eigentlich der Sinn des Lebens ist. Lasst uns reden, reflektieren, lachen, weinen und gemeinsam das Leben ergründen.

title: PolyMoly!
description:
Hey daar! Wij zijn Louie (die/hij) en Manon (zij/haar), en we gaan al bijna drie jaar sterk als koppel. Maar we zijn niet zomaar een doorsnee paar – we zijn druk bezig met het verkennen van de wereld van ethische non-monogamie en polyamorie binnen onze relatie. En laten we eerlijk zijn, dat is soms best wel een kronkelige weg. We misten de ervaringen van anderen en inzichten tijdens dit avontuur, dus hebben we besloten om deze podcast te lanceren. "If you dont't see the change, be the change."

Ons doel? We willen graag onze frisse, nieuwe ervaringen met jou delen en hopen dat jij er ook iets uit kunt halen. Maar dat is niet alles. Naast het duiken in de wereld van ethische non-monogamie en polyamorie, snijden we ook regelmatig andere onderwerpen aan die gerelateerd zijn aan de LGBTQIAP+ gemeenschap.

Maar, en dit is belangrijk, we willen wel even duidelijk maken dat we niet de alleswetende experts zijn. In feite nemen we je mee in ons proces terwijl we zelf nog aan het ontdekken zijn. We weten dat we onderweg tegen allerlei uitdagingen gaan aanlopen. Dus, neem alsjeblieft niet alles wat we zeggen als dé onwrikbare waarheid, maar eerder als onze gedachten en bevindingen op dat moment.

Als je nog dieper in de onderwerpen wilt duiken die we bespreken, raden we je zeker aan om naast onze podcast ook andere bronnen te raadplegen. Hoe dan ook, we hopen dat je ontzettend veel plezier beleeft aan het luisteren naar onze gesprekken!

Oh, en vergeet niet om ons te volgen:

https://instagram.com/polymolydepodcast?igshid=MzNlNGNkZWQ4Mg==

title: Journey of Drifting Clouds
description:
Hi. I am Kumi and I am an office worker and an End-of-Life Doula.
Sharing stories has some healing effects and it allows me to feel more… Through my losses, I’ve learned that feeling the feelings is the only way for me to cope and move forward, so I decided to talk about my journey of grief and loss and many other things.
So yes, this is a place for me to become vulnerable but at the same time, I become real as well. I’m happy to share.
It’s not just the death that we experience grief from. We experience all kinds of losses, changes and adjustments here and there… and grief is ultimately necessary in our lives to feel joy and love…
But grief is powerful and we tend to numb it..And it is something we hardly ever talk about. So I’m here to talk more!
I will be doing this podcast in two languages - English and Japanese. 
I also would like to be a resource point to the Japanese community predominantly in the metro Vancouver area. 
Last but not least, if you’d like to share your stories of loss and grief, please send me a message! We can talk on the Podcast together or I would be happy to read out your story where you have options of being anonymous as well.

title: The Behaveo Show
description:
Evidence-based mental health insights and interviews with former patients and professionals who are collectively re-designing the broken system for good.

Welcome to The Behaveo Show podcast, hosted by former psychiatric nurse, Charlie Penwarden, now mental health consultant at Behaveo. In this podcast, Charlie delves into the darker and less 'fluffy' side of mental health, bringing to light the challenges and struggles that individuals with mental illness face on a daily basis.

As a former psychiatric nurse, Charlie has spent years working closely with individuals who suffer from mental illness, and has seen firsthand the impact it can have on their lives and the lives of those around them. In The Behaveo Show, Charlie draws on his extensive experience and expertise to explore a range of mental health issues, from depression and anxiety to more complex disorders such as borderline personality disorder and schizophrenia.

But this is not just another mental health podcast. The Behaveo Show goes deeper, exploring the often-overlooked realities of mental illness, and addressing topics that are often stigmatized or ignored. Through candid interviews with guests, Charlie uncovers the raw truth about mental illness, and offers practical advice and insights for those who may be struggling themselves, or who are supporting someone with mental illness. Whether you're a mental health professional, someone who has been affected by mental illness, or simply interested in learning more about the fascinating topic of human behaviour important topic, The Behaveo Show is here for you.

Join Charlie on this journey to uncover the truth about mental health, and discover new ways to support yourself or others on the road to recovery. www.behaveo.com/podcast

description:
During these podcast episodes we will be reviewing pretty much anything and everything. Every possible topic is up for discussion and we lay it all out, no topic is off limits. And here’s the twist: all of this will be reviewed from the perspective of a MINORITY

With these podcast episodes I would like to create a space where we can exchange our stories in relation to the episode-of-the-week review by exchanging the many ways that is has moved us, be it positively: by helping us through dark times, or negatively: by possibly triggering us or forcing us to face some harsh truths about the world and or ourselves.

My wish is to create a place and create space to offer support, share and where together we create a community where that is the focus of our story - the many ways we are connected.

FunFact: I myself am both a survivor and therapist! And all of the different avenues of my life mentioned in the Introduction will be touched upon and shared as we are reviewing.

Who said a podcast can't be both Educational and Fun?

For more, also see: https://www.instagram.com/lets.review.with.layla.and.you/

Hope to see ya back for more! 🔥

title: Libro de los Abrazos
description:
Libro de los Abrazos de Eduardo Galeano.

Eduardo Galeano (nace el 03 de Septiembre de 1940 y muere 13 de Abril de 2015) fue un prolífico escritor uruguayo nacido en Montevideo. Su compromiso con latinoamérica y el mundo lo hizo conocido por el libro "Las Venas Abiertas de América Latina". Escribió, prosa, poesía, entre las cuales se encuentra "El libro de los abrazos" el cual es un compendio de breves relatos que abarcan diversos temas como cultura, sociedad o literatura.

En este Podcast se leerán algunos de sus poemas.

Así que te invito a que te pongas cómodo y te dejes abrazar por su poesía.

title: The Gather with Deanne Oliver-Pickard
description:
Deanne founded 'The Gather' - a women's platform for connection and community in Brighton & Hove in January 2022 - off the back of coming out of the weirdness of lockdown and wanting to re-connect with wonderful women, to share stories, to find a tribe and to create a platform for solidarity.

The Gather hosts monthly meet ups, discussing themes in circle with women and inviting in various guests to share their own journeys, their work and their insight to help support the topic.

The evenings are very relaxed, wine is consumed (although doesn't need to be), chocolates are nibbled, laughter is always present, sometimes tears, a wealth of sharing, outpourings of love and support...we always go off theme and then come back to it but each event has had one thing in common...the pure unadulterated magic that occurs when women gather.

These podcasts are a way of showcasing and expanding on the conversations had in a little cosy space in Hove, inviting in some of the guests to join Deanne in chatting more about topics that need to be talked about and we hope that you enjoy them as much as we did IRL.

This podcast launches on International Women's Day 2023 as, well it just makes so much sense.

www.instagram.com/this.is.the.gather

title: Can't Relate
description:
This is a show for the ones who feel like they don’t quite belong.

Emily Dukes is no stranger to feeling like an outsider. With a unique upbringing that left her feeling like the odd one out, she’s still searching for her place and voice even as a late 20-something. No topic is off-limits on this lifestyle show, covering everything from the familiar themes you know and love like friendships, relationships, and routines, to the more messy issues like mental health, trauma, leaving religion, questioning values, and more.

No longer is Dukes trying to fit in at the cool kids’ table; she’s set her own table, where anyone and everyone is welcome to pull up a chair and join the conversation. You belong here.

title: Our Roots, Our Stories: High Schoolers Share Cultural Experiences
description:
At Western Reserve Academy (WRA), students possess a multitude of diverse cultural experiences from across the country and even the world. Senior Elba Heddesheimer created the Our Roots, Our Stories podcast to share these stories with her school community. We hope to provide students with the platform to voice their unique cultural perspectives and experiences.

Each episode features a 3-5 minute story from one of our students that was shared at a February storytelling night in the Green Key. These heartwarming stories touch on their hometowns, their experiences at WRA, and the realizations they’ve made through self-reflection. The first few episodes relate to the theme, 'Places We Call Home,' but we're excited to explore other themes in the future.

Storytelling is a powerful tool for fostering cross-cultural competency and understanding. We encourage all WRA students to attend the next storytelling night on April 7 from 6:30-7:30 in the Green Key. Students will reflect on the theme “Transitions,” discussing the changes and challenges they have faced while navigating life.

So if you're a student at WRA, I invite you to join us in celebrating our diverse community and the incredible stories that come with it.

Contact the Host?

title: Evoyoution Podcast
description:
Ausgewandert und was nun? Wer bin ich eigentlich ohne meine gewohnte Umgebung, Freunde und Familie? Wieso fühle ich mich im Job auf einmal wie ein Anfänger? Warum fühle ich mich so verloren? Was will ich eigentlich mit meinem Leben machen? Wie komme ich aus dem “funktionieren” ins “leben”? Warum fühle ich mich mit allem überfordert?

Und die größte Fragen von allen: Wieso weiss ich nicht mehr wer ich eigentlich bin?

Dieser Podcast ist für alle Frauen, die (vielleicht) ausgewandert sind, sich selbst nicht mehr vertrauen, feststecken, und nach Lösungen suchen, um aus diesem Loch wieder rauszukommen. Egal ob du im Ausland lebst oder eine Identitätskrise in der Heimat hast, diese Show ist für dich.

title: Sans mode d'emploi
description:
Avec SANS MODE D’EMPLOI, la réalisatrice Vanessa Gauvin-Brodeur explore le monde du travail en constante évolution, et tout particulièrement le monde de la pige au sein de l’industrie créative : musiciens, réals, auteurs, artistes visuels, mais aussi des entrepreneurs (parfois issus de milieux plus traditionnels) ayant créé leur propre vision d’une carrière épanouie.

Ces métiers aux multiples facettes, aussi excitants que complexes à exercer, viennent sans aucune instruction. Ils sont remplis d’incertitudes, de hauts et de bas, et demandent souvent à ceux qui les exercent une résilience hors du commun.

De façon informelle et décontractée, l'animatrice invite ses amis pigistes à discuter à cœur ouvert des joies, des découvertes, et des difficultés de leur profession, de tout ce qu’on ne dit (généralement) pas sur la pige et le milieu de la création, de leur vision et relation avec leur travail en particulier, et avec le monde du travail en général.

SANS MODE D'EMPLOI est un balado pour tout ceux qui s’intéressent au monde du travail redéfini, et souhaitent décortiquer sans tabou ni préjugé ce qui nous angoisse et nous émerveille de cette nouvelle réalité professionnelle en pleine expansion.

Description: In Edumacated, we interview special guests to learn about their journey in education and the lessons they've learned ON the job. Join us as we explore the meaning of "edumacated" and how it shapes the work we do in our region of schools in San Diego.

Topics Covered:

  • Our guest's journey in education as a student and a teacher
  • The challenges and lessons learned in the field of education
  • The importance of lifelong learning in education
  • The meaning of "edumacated" and how it shapes our work as educators

About the Podcast: Edumacated is a podcast by and for L4L team members in the San Diego region who are passionate about education and lifelong learning. Join us as we explore the paths of other educators and learn from their experiences in the field.

Subscribe and Follow Us: Don't miss an episode of Edumacated! Subscribe to our podcast on Apple Podcasts, Spotify, or your favorite podcast app.

Welcome to "Beyond the Party," a podcast that goes beyond the glitz and glamor of the nightlife industry. Join us as we dive into the personal stories of those who work in the industry and discuss the challenges and triumphs they face.

From bartenders, club owners, and DJs to event planners and promoters, we will explore the daily struggles and highs of life in the nightlife world. Our guests will share their experiences with navigating relationships, finances, and mental health while working in an industry that never sleeps.

But this podcast isn't just about the nightlife industry. We will also tackle everyday life issues and offer solutions for listeners who may be facing similar challenges.

Most importantly, we will discuss the path to success and share stories of those who have made it big in the industry, offering insights and advice to listeners who aspire to do the same.

Join us every week for a candid and insightful conversation on the nightlife industry.

So sit back, grab a drink, and let's go Beyond the Party.

title: Doxxed The Podcast
description:
Join our private podcast feed with members only content here:

https://doxxedthepodcast.supercast.com/

Doxxed the Podcast, hosted by Jane Bonis and Roxy Renee, is a powerful and eye-opening exploration of the often-overlooked world of online harassment and targeting. With personal stories, expert insights, and practical strategies for healing and prevention, Jane and Roxy provide a safe and supportive space for those who have experienced cyberbullying, gang stalking, drama farming, smear campaigns, and doxxing. Each episode of Doxxed the Podcast offers a compassionate yet hard-hitting look at the devastating impact of online targeting, and seeks to inspire change within our society. With a focus on hope, encouragement, and preparedness, Jane and Roxy aim to empower their listeners to stand up against online harassment and build a safer, more respectful online community. From interviews with survivors and experts, to practical tips and resources for staying safe online, Doxxed the Podcast is a must-listen for anyone who has been or may become a target of online harassment. Join Jane and Roxy as they shed light on this critical issue and work towards a brighter, safer future for us all.

I may touch on my health and health concern as a person with Hidradenitis Suppurativa a chronic autoimmune disease/overactive immune disease. Much like Let's Hablar Podcast I will discuss pop culture alongside my self love journey and growth as a person. I will add some content from social media other avenues as needed while other interesting topics are being developed. On Let's Hablar Solita Podcast I will shout out organizations along with brands or creators that I support. This is a Spanglish podcast, and hablemos de todo.

title: Stepping Out the Box
description:
"Stepping Out of the Box" is a dynamic and engaging podcast that covers a wide range of topics, including religion, world and local news, politics, sports, and life in general. Hosted by Uncle Daddy PopPop and Chuckee, this variety podcast takes listeners on a journey through various subjects, offering unique perspectives and insights along the way.

As Uncle Daddy PopPop likes to say, he's not just hosting the show by himself; his best friends God and Jesus are along for the ride too. With a deep commitment to faith and spirituality, the show often explores religious themes and offers thoughtful reflections on the role of religion in contemporary society.

But "Stepping Out of the Box" is more than just a religious podcast - it's a show that tackles a diverse range of issues and perspectives, always with a sense of humor and openness to new ideas. Whether you're interested in current events, sports, or just looking for some insightful commentary on the human experience, this podcast has something for everyone. So come join Uncle Daddy PopPop and his friends on this journey through life - you never know what you might learn along the way.

description:
We've got love for you if you were born in the 80s! Millennials unite. Haika & Mutesh are here to talk about all the things that keep us up at night, like how to find a job that pays enough to afford rent, or whether it's cool to still be on Facebook (It's not) and so much more. We're the generation that's always on the go, always connected, and always a little bit confused about what we're doing with our lives.

But hey, at least we've got memes, right? And we're not afraid to use them. Our show is full of hot takes, hilarious anecdotes, and the occasional existential crisis. Because let's be real, being a millennial isn't all sunshine and rainbows. We'll be sharing our hilarious struggles with dating, social media, and trying to save enough money for that one day we can finally retire.

So buckle up, grab your phone (it's probably already in your hand, let's be real), and join us for the ride. We promise to keep it real, and keep it 100% millennial.

Thanks for listening!

title: Pridefinder: The Rainbow Road Trip Podcast
description:
Pridefinder – The Rainbow Road Trip was a travelling podcast project commissioned during the 2023 Midsumma Festival as part of the State Government's initiative, Victoria’s Pride.

Helene Thomas; an award winning creative audio producer, journalist, and queer ally, developed a mobile story studio with the purpose of encouraging connection, cultivating empathy and preserving peoples experiences.

As much of Victoria’s queer history relies on verbal recount, Midsumma, Helene and the Pridefinder connected with regionally living LGBTQIA+ Victorians to help capture their unique stories.

Throughout this series you will hear first-hand, the successes, hopes, dreams, fears and struggles of diverse members of the community.
