description:
Welcome to "The Paternity Press", a podcast that documents the journey of becoming a dad. Join your host, John Warder, a first-time father, as he narrates his experiences from anticipating the arrival of his daughter to becoming a full-fledged girl dad.

From diapers to first steps, he'll take you on the front lines of fatherhood with honest conversations, a few dad jokes, and interviews with fellow fathers. With humor and candor, John explores the challenges and joys of raising a child and offers insights for other dads who are on the same journey.

Whether you're a new dad, a seasoned pro, or just curious about what parenthood is really like, "The Paternity Press" is the podcast for you. So grab a cup of coffee, sit back, and join John as he navigates the exciting and sometimes overwhelming world of fatherhood.

title: NOT FOR MY VILLAGE PEOPLE- Esther A
description:
Life is about experiences, you can't hold on to everything ~S.A.A

I've receive so much from life and so the intention of this podcast is to let out those experiences with the hopes of inspiring at least one person. I bring to you a labour of love on my humble beginnings, relationships, career and as an entrepreneur.

If at any point my H-FACTOR rears it ugly head just act like you didnt hear it. LOL

*H-factor: A typical manifestation usually observed among the Yorùbá people — an ethnic group of southwestern and North-central Nigeria as well as southern and central Benin, together known as Yorùbáland. Examples of H-factor manifestations include saying 'hegg' instead of 'egg,' or saying 'amburger,' instead of 'hamburger.

*Village people: The phrase “Village People”to me means naysayers, evildoers, haters, narrow minded, judgemental people etc.,

I intend to have fun and sometimes cringe to the listening of my own voice but still get the message out.

It’s already looking like a challenging territory but no one grows in their comfort zone. So, welcome to “Not for my village people podcast” my 2023 way to disrupt my comfort zone and learn some new lessons as I progress, learn and improve.

title: Coco to Coca | Hermandad y Crecimiento
description:
Coco to Coca: Hermandad y Crecimiento es un podcast inspirador que narra la historia única de dos hermanos, Jorge y Luis, cuyas vidas han sido marcadas por un desafío extraordinario. A los 7 años, Jorge sufrió un accidente eléctrico que le arrebató ambos brazos, cambiando el rumbo de nuestras vidas para siempre. Esta experiencia no solo ha sido un reto para él, sino también para mí, Luis, como su hermano mayor y para nuestra familia.

A través de Coco to Coca, deseamos compartir con el mundo nuestras experiencias, nuestras luchas y nuestros triunfos. Es una ventana hacia nuestra vida y una oportunidad para demostrar que las adversidades no nos han definido, sino que nos han fortalecido.

Pero hay más en nuestra historia. A los 18 años, Luis se mudó a otro país, separándome de Jorge durante casi una década. Durante ese tiempo, nos convertimos en extraños el uno para el otro. Ahora, en este podcast, nos embarcamos en un viaje de reencuentro y descubrimiento mutuo, explorando cómo hemos crecido como individuos mientras estábamos separados.

Únete a nosotros en Coco to Coca: Hermandad y Crecimiento, donde compartiremos conversaciones sinceras, reflexiones profundas y momentos de inspiración. Aquí, Jorge y Luis revelarán las lecciones que han aprendido y cómo han encontrado la fuerza para enfrentar los desafíos que la vida les ha presentado.

Desde la superación personal hasta el amor fraternal, este podcast desafiará las expectativas y mostrará que el amor y la determinación pueden vencer cualquier obstáculo.

¡Te invitamos a ser parte de nuestra historia en Coco to Coca: Hermandad y Crecimiento! Juntos, romperemos barreras y demostraremos que la resiliencia y la unión familiar pueden transformar vidas

title: The Nothing Show
description:
Welcome to "The Nothing Show," the podcast that skillfully balances humor and seriousness while delving into the intricacies of society and our everyday lives. Join me, your host, as I take you on a unique journey where we discuss the world around us, its quirks, and how it influences our daily experiences.

In each episode of "The Nothing Show," we tackle pressing social issues, cultural phenomena, and the latest happenings that shape our collective existence. Whether it's dissecting political trends, examining the impact of technology, or analyzing societal norms, we dive deep into the topics that affect us all. Through thoughtful discussions and insightful commentary, we explore the ways in which these issues intersect with our lives, shedding light on their significance.

But don't be fooled by the seriousness—this show knows how to have fun! "The Nothing Show" is designed to be an entertaining and engaging escape from the mundane. Expect witty banter, humorous anecdotes, and lighthearted segments that provide a refreshing break from the seriousness of the world. It's the perfect blend of laughter and introspection, creating an enjoyable listening experience for those seeking a respite from their day-to-day routine.

Think of "The Nothing Show" as your personal venting session. As your host, I share my own thoughts, frustrations, and observations about the world, creating a safe space for listeners to relate, empathize, and join in on the conversation. Whether it's a hilarious encounter with a self-checkout machine or a serious discussion about the impact of social media on mental health, we explore both the trivial and profound aspects of life, giving a voice to the things we all experience but rarely discuss.

This podcast is for everyone who enjoys thought-provoking conversations, witty humor, and relatable rants. Whether you're commuting, taking a break, or just looking for something to pass the time, "The Nothing Show" is here to keep you company. So sit back, relax, and let's embark on this rollercoaster of laughter, introspection, and everything in between.

Remember, life is full of moments that may seem like nothing at first glance, but hold profound meaning. In "The Nothing Show," we celebrate the mundane, find humor in the chaos, and shed light on the profound implications of the seemingly insignificant. It's a podcast that invites you to laugh, reflect, and be a part of the ever-changing tapestry of our society. Welcome to "The Nothing Show"—where talking about everything and nothing specific is the heart and soul of our captivating journey together.

It's not all about dementia though, hence the 'other stories' element. In other stories, we discuss how each of us is an idiot at some point in our lives, we take it in turns to share our stupidity. We hope you enjoy and that it gives you a laugh now and then, because we could all do with laughter in our lives.

I was interviewing so many Moms and inmates, that I became heartsick. I had to stop because it was killing me emotionally. RSS is where I started and this is where I will stay. This inaugural podcast is my daughter's story and what I want this relaunch to be. My mission is prison reform. People are waking up about our Penal System and I am here to help you to fully understand what we all go through when we have a loved one behind bars. So, with that, welcome to Invisible Chains.

title: Classified Conversations
description: Welcome to Classified Conversations. Are you tired of all the mainstream cookie cutter podcasts? Looking for something raw, real and uncut? Something that deals with real life issues, stories, experiences and perspectives without filters, censors or apologies? Go ahead and toss your box of tissues in the trash and buckle up for Classified Conversations, a place where we dive deep into the issues we deal with today, the history that makes us who we are and the real shit that makes us tick. If you’re craving something different, funny, sarcastic, then join me, a regular guy somewhere in Southwest Florida, contemplating everything. Bring your experiences and share them here in a community of like-minded individuals who want to bring back honesty and real talk in a world where truth is going extinct. Join Classified Conversations, a place where we can be ourselves and remember the experiences that made us the people we are today, what means the most to us in this crazy life. The low times, heartache and pain, the highs and joys that we'll never forget...all those things that influenced and shaped us as human beings -- bring them here. Let's discuss. Join the conversation.

title: Hope Ahead: A Journey of Infertility
description:
Hope Ahead is a husband's & wife's perspectives of being unable to conceive after a miscarriage. We hope this story/journey will glorify God & be encouraging to those who are currently dealing with or have dealt with infertility. We also hope that this will be informative to friends or family of those involved who don't know what to to say or do during this season. We pray for God to use this time in our lives to draw us & you closer to Him & to the ultimate purpose He has for us. We will pray during each podcast for God's will & blessing over this situation & give a scripture related to the topics discussed. This journey isn't easy, but knowing you aren't alone, and having an outlet to share and talk about it is a step towards healing. Often times, we suffer in silence and don't know how to talk about it. We also hope that this will bring more awareness to the issue and classification of "infertility" and provide more discussions and funding to work towards a better future for those of us in the "20%."

To watch our podcasts on video, find us @hopeaheadjourney on YouTube

Descubre cómo cultivar una mayor conciencia de ti mismo, desarrollar habilidades emocionales y encontrar la paz interior en medio del caos de la vida moderna. ¡Acompáñanos mientras exploramos el camino hacia una vida más plena y consciente!

title: Stories For Ahmed
description:
Welcome to "Stories for Ahmed," by Dr. Lacey, a podcast born from a deep friendship, countless adventures, and an unyielding passion for storytelling. This show peels back the layers of Dr. Lacey's colourful life, chronicling the laughter, tears, triumphs, and trials that have shaped her journey.

Dr. Lacey, a natural storyteller and entertainer, opens her vast trove of life experiences to captivate you with tales from different eras of her life. Each episode, carefully curated and woven into an audio tapestry, promises to take you on a wild ride through unexpected turns, teaching lessons, evoking emotions, and most importantly, celebrating life.

One of the most ardent fans of Dr. Lacey's stories is her dear friend, Ahmed. His fascination and intrigue with her tales inspired the birth of this podcast. Every story told here has been a part of their shared memories, whispered secrets in hushed tones, or loud laughter echoing in rooms. And now, these stories are brought to life for all to enjoy. Whether you're a friend, family, or a curious listener, each episode offers a window into the extraordinary life of Dr. Lacey.

Expect heartwarming anecdotes, hilarious misadventures, stories of love and loss, and the wisdom that comes from a lifetime of learning. From her childhood escapades to her scholarly pursuits, her travels around the globe to the quiet moments of introspection, there's a story for everyone here. This podcast, above all, cherishes human connection and the magic of shared stories.

While "Stories for Ahmed" is indeed a tribute to a beautiful friendship, it's also an invitation for every listener to step into the shoes of Dr. Lacey and experience the world from her perspective. Join us in this intimate exploration of life's many wonders and oddities, and be ready to see the world anew.

So grab a cup of coffee, find a comfortable spot, and let Dr. Lacey's enchanting voice take you on a journey like no other. Welcome to "Stories for Ahmed, by Dr. Lacey". Let the adventure begin!

title: Unleashed Strength
description: Martial arts saved my life. It became my daily refuge, a lifeline that pulled me out of the depths of depression and helped me confront the hidden diseases that often go unnoticed. Through this podcast, I want to shine a light on the often overlooked benefits of martial arts for people facing their own battles.

title: Unveiling Reflections
description: Welcome to "Unveiling Reflections," the podcast where we embark on a transformative journey towards self-love, growth, and building our foundation on faith. I'm your host, Faith, a young creative and multifaceted woman who's here to share her experiences, insights, and lessons learned along the winding path of adulthood, living with sickle cell, navigating graduate school, and my journey to medical school. Remember, always live by faith, through grace, and embrace your inner light, unveiling your reflections🪞

title: The Megan May Podcast
description: Hey everyone, welcome to the Megan May Podcast! I am your host, Megan May and I am so excited you are here! I am a wife, mom to 4, entrepreneur, small-town girl, people pleaser in rehab, faith follower, and just your average girl next door. Enough with the small talk, let’s dig deep. I am excited to share with you in this space real and imperfect episodes of marriage, mom life, relationships, faith, adoption and so much more! And more than anything I hope to inspire you to truly know how much you matter in this world. So grab a cozy spot, blanket, snack, or beverage of your choice and come exactly as you are, and let's get started!

I think it is important to continuously reflect on who I am, and the person I am trying to be, and create goals and positive habits that will align me with that version of myself. "Stay Aligned" is like a reminder, or a mantra, or even an affirmation, that remind me why it is important to always be intentional with my life choices. It's just a reminder to make the decisions that is in alignment with my best self.

description:
Have you ever been scared to do something that you thought you wouldn’t be good at? Short for me is, YES! I have thought about creating a podcast for about a year or so but I was scared to step out of my comfort zone and I was scared to also put myself out there. Sometimes you just got to do it!

Here at Coffee + Convos we will talk about self-care, mental health, motherhood, accountability, careers and so much more. SO grab your coffee mugs and join me for a virtual coffee date!

The purpose of this podcast is to connect with people that need that little bit of encouragement or empowerment to keep going. I have several people lined up that I will bring on the show to discuss their life and what they had to go thru to get to where they are now. You’d be surprised at the things that people face behind closed doors.

Stay tuned for all the episodes to come! I look forward to connecting with everyone and I hope that this podcast helps you on your journey.

title: Live and Let Live
description:
it's a weird saying "it is what it is", but for most of us, hearing it from someone; friend, family or co-worker; brings an almost sad sense of "they've seen some shit". A common saying among people, who at some point have or are on the verge of giving up, it's also a mantra of the strong. A sense that no matter what happens, things will work out, and somehow you will get through it. It is of course what it is.

​

Love sucks...so does everything that comes with it. The joy, the memories and the eventual breakup. Where the memories formed become a reminder of what you had, the plans and ideas you shared with that special someone sting more then ever; in a timeless void of "shoulda, coulda, woulda." Of course, seeing a former partner, girlfriend, boyfriend etc happy is all you really want at the end of the day. Weather its with or without you. While fostering and attempting to grow a friendship and keep the bond strong in whatever manner you can has its struggles and a daily reminder of what could have been, the bonds to friendship come with the same unique struggles.

​

This episode is my personal journey through a love found in the most unlikely of places (Grindr), to the good times and memories built, to post break-up and the daily struggle to split what was and what is. An hour long talk of how my former relationship changed me for the good the bad and the ugly, and the gratitude that I have daily that the individual is still in my life. Weather with me as a partner or friend. How do you deal with breakups and how do you; over time; numb the heartache and flashbacks of the small traditions, memories and things that make you laugh?

title: Life, The Universe, and Dan
description:
I have always been naturally curious about life and the universe.

My parents nurtured and encouraged this curiosity, especially my father, who was an engineer with a keen understanding of physics. He loved explaining the mysteries of the cosmos to me, and one particular conversation turned my curiosity into a lifelong obsession with knowledge and learning.

After the death of my brother in 2018, my curiosity turned into a passion. As I dealt with my own experience of grief and pain, I became fascinated with life and death. I have since explored what it's been like to go through addiction, death, and divorce.

I have come to a place of acceptance and peace around not only my brother's death, but many of life's anxieties.

My curiosity now takes me on a journey to understand what it has been like for those around me to experience life and death.

In my podcast, I talk to friends and family about their lives and what it was like to lose our dear friend and brother, Dan. I explore many topics, including death and suicide.

I encourage you to listen with an open heart, but be prepared that the subject matter can be difficult at times. Go gently

title: Living with Leukaemia
description:
Raising Awareness For ALL

Kicking Cancers Butt 💙🌈🎗️💪🏼

Remission 2/3/23

End of treatment date 27/4/26

Summary -

Monthly podcast.

A heartfelt story about 9 year old Archie, and his families journey living with Leukaemia.

Join us for the highs and lows and everything in between.

In this episode, Natalie discusses how she first saw the signs in Archie and how she attempted to find out what was wrong.

Appointments, living day to day life and not knowing what was happening, why and what to expect.

Speaking with doctors, balancing work and hospital appointments is one part of this story for Archie and his family.

This story not only affects Archie, who is battling everyday through Leukaemia but those around him and how they take each day as it comes.

We have Natalie, Archie's mum, Olivia, Archie's sister, Harry, Archie's brother, then Archie's dad, Baz, grandfather Colin and grandmother Michelle and everyone else in-between.

As Natalie discusses her struggles, losses and wins, we see an insight into a mothers side of the story and her pain to overcome the odds.

With each step, one door closes and another opens with Natalie, Archie and the family, when they eventually found out the news they weren't expecting.

This podcast will try to help those that may have just started their journey, at any stage or if it is a friend or family to answer any questions, fears and reassure and support those that may be going through this themselves or alone.

There will be links below for support groups and for further information on Archie's journey and linked charities and groups.

There will be laughs and smiles and not just doom and gloom. This is a raw, honest and open discussion where there is no taboo subject.

We hope you enjoy the podcast and join us on this monthly journey to document, discuss, answer and share Archie's story, Living with Leukaemia.

title: The Lipoedema Podcast
description:
Unlike any other podcast in Australia, "The Lipoedema Podcast" sets out to provide invaluable insights into this condition from two distinct perspectives. Shelley approaches lipoedema through a conservative management approach, while Tiana bravely shares her journey through surgical intervention. By sharing their stories, experiences, and knowledge, they aim to support, inform, and empower individuals dealing with this condition.

The podcast will feature expert guests from the medical community, including professionals specializing in Lipoedema treatment, as well as inspiring women living with Lipoedema. Listeners can expect discussions on various topics, including nutrition, lymphatic drainage, compression therapy, surgical interventions, and touching personal accounts of individuals overcoming the challenges posed by lipoedema.

title: Talkin Story
description:
The Talkin Story podcast is a new project of Well Organized/Black Lives Matter of Jefferson County. It features local people of the global majority (PGM) who are quietly acting as flashpoints for social and cultural transformation within Port Townsend/East Jefferson county. These are the people who have been steadily working almost under the radar to craft a world in which they exist with sovereignty and creativity. They may or may not be in designated leadership roles, but their very existence is a source of inspiration and a touchstone within the PGM community primarily and the broader community as well.

The first season of this intergenerational podcast is co-hosted by Oceana Sawyer, Ezra Kikue Cook, and Lorenzo McCleese.

Oceana is an eldering person of African descent who moves in the liminal spaces of life & death, capture & liberation. They are a poet and a writer with a vision of community of local PGM that has the capacity to navigate the reality of liquid modernity.

Ezra is an ever changing force for change. As much as they talk, you'll never really understand them. His look is always changing and his list of passions is always expanding. Professionally he is known for working at Centrum for the last three years as both a grip and a videographer/broadcast technician. Ezra has years of experience in theater tech, acting, and media production. They are a writer and director with dreams of putting out original films on the big screen. They believe in the importance of advocacy and integrity- the fight for what is right at the small level. They are particularly involved in activism for Queer and Transgender support systems at the local level. Ezra is the eldest son of James Cook, born in Yokohama Japan, and Mirandy Cook, born in the United States. Working on this podcast has helped him to connect to his Japanese American heritage and BIPOC identity.

Lorenzo is a recent graduate from Port Townsend High School (PTHS) and a freshman at the University of Washington (UW). He has done work for the BIPOC Family Excursion Program, PTHS BIPOC Student Union, and most recently, been a host on the Talkin’ Story Podcast.

Being born & raised in Port Townsend, Lorenzo is eager to move out to Seattle and study Environmental Science. He hopes to continue engaging with his passion for equity and diversity in Seattle. Lorenzo is a member of the 7th cohort of UW’s Brotherhood Initiative; a program that provides opportunities for academic growth and leadership for underrepresented men of color.

title: The Other Russian
description:
The inspiration for this podcast came from Raghavendra, a friend I met in India in 2012 through couchsurfing. Our bond grew over the years, and during a trip to India in 2023, he suggested I start a podcast. Despite being jetlagged and high, I embraced the idea. My wife was initially hesitant due to concerns about quality, but I decided to dive in and improve as I go.

A bit about me: I was born in Sverdlovsk, now Ekaterinburg, known for its historical significance and as a cultural crossroad between Europe and Asia. My upbringing was challenging. After the 1998 economic crisis, my father turned to alcohol, leading to his separation from our family when I was 13. My mother worked multiple jobs to support us. I wasn't academically inclined, but my mother's guidance led me to study project management at Ural State Technical University. During my studies, my sister introduced me to the Work&Travel program in the USA. My trip to Maine in 2006 was transformative, exposing me to a new culture and broadening my horizons. After university, I also earned a military degree, ironically in bridge-building, given my humanities background.

This is just the beginning of my story, and I have much more to share.

The topics that I plan to cover in this podcast: politics, psychedelics, feminism, marketing, business, sex, drugs, music, philosophy, change, humans, etc.
